Yes, we are clear on the responsibilities. Please see a simplified breakdown below for alignment:

🔹 Enterprise DevOps

This team are the administrators and owners of the DevOps toolset (e.g., GitHub, Jenkins, Artifactory, etc.).

They are responsible for:

Tool administration and governance

Access management (GitHub, Jenkins, etc.)

Infrastructure issues related to DevOps tools

Server availability and platform-level problems

Upgrades, maintenance, and configuration at tool level

In short:
They manage and maintain the DevOps platforms themselves.

🔹 BAU DevOps

This team owns the CI/CD pipelines and their configurations.

They are responsible for:

Pipeline setup and maintenance

Build and deployment configurations

Fixing pipeline failures

Supporting application teams during deployments

In short:
They ensure applications are built and deployed correctly using the tools.

If there is any failure during a release pipeline execution, BAU DevOps investigates and resolves it.

🔹 Release Engineers

This team manages the release execution process.

They are responsible for:

Creating release folders/branches

Triggering release pipelines (e.g., via GitHub Actions)

Coordinating release activities

In short:
They initiate and coordinate releases, but do not maintain the pipelines or tools.

🔄 Simple Responsibility Flow

Tool/platform issue → Enterprise DevOps

Pipeline/configuration issue → BAU DevOps

Release execution/trigger → Release Engineers

Release failure → BAU DevOps to investigate

